fermilisp -- a portable lisp interpreter
========================================

FermiLisp is a FREE Public Domain Lisp interpreter made mainly for FermiOS, but portable on basically
any operating system that supports C.

It is written in C99 and supports most stuff you'd expect from a basic LISP system, and can be embedded on many applications.

BUILDING
========

Use make. Both gmake and bmake work, but bmake is preferred. You'll only need a C compiler:

	$ make
	cc ...
	cc ...
	cc ...

	...

If everthing goes OK, a ./flisp executable will appear. Install it with:

	# make install

(NOTE: run as root). You can uninstall with:

	# make uninstall

